 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2991<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 6:19:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=565.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: If i am not a cannipetting mage is switch to Evoc. best </span><hr size=1> I understand and respect the arguments in favor of evocation, but I already switched once and am sticking with conjuration.  I still chain pets in groups, for crowd control or in pet/caster groups, and of course I have converted to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The Gospel of Improved Reclaim Energy</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
