<br>
Narrow range? Well, that is very subjective. FoT and Rains are 90% of what some of us do in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>almost all</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> combat situations that we choose. For those for which this is true, evocation remains the optional choice. If in an average 4 hour hunting group, I re-summon a pet maybe once, cast CoH maybe twice, but cast FoT perhaps 300-400 times, you'd be hard pressed to tell me evocation is not the best choice here. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Horses for courses.<br>
<br>
&quot;I find both bolts and rains to be unreliable.. &quot;<br>
<br>
Well, again, very subjective. Some of us don't. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
To the original poster, yes, if you don't canni pets, like I don't, and if you are more solo/group oriented and not raid focused, and especially if you like bolts and rains like I do, evocation is a good choice.<br>
<br>
Suzanna. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 2765<br> <font color=#333333>(3/5/03 12:45:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=565.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: If i am not a cannipetting mage is switch to Evoc. best </span><hr size=1> Of course.  That is why some mages choose Evocation.  If bolts and rains are what you find yourself using almost exclusively, then it makes sense to optimize yourself for that style of play.<br>
<br>
My point is that it is entirely focused on saving mana on damage spells.  To that end, if bolts and rains aren't a problem for you, it is the best damage per mana you will get.  Conjuration helps you on the dd spells that Evoc does not, and also helps you in a multitude of other areas.  I consider that more balanced and versatile, though it sacrifices the maximum damage per mana potential of FoT and Sun Storm. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skildpade>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#333333>(3/5/03 1:01:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=565.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: If i am not a cannipetting mage is switch to Evoc. best </span><hr size=1> You could also argue that you should switch to alteration, at least for raiding. Lately in groups and multi groups/raids I have found myself almost exclusively casting mala/malosini. Granted at lv 60 I am one of the four highest people in my guild and none of the other lv 60 are shamans with malo. When the pulls are really comming in it is easy to use a lot of mana simply debuffing.<br>
